ovide precise measurements of the cosmic evolution of alpha\nthat include quantitative constraints on systematic errors. Application of this\ntechnique is limited only by the detectability of |tau|~0.01 OH lines toward\nradio continuum sources and may be possible to z~5.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 May 2004 20:50:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
